â?¢ TSUNAMi (i.e. inaugural call)
â?¢ NCL
â?¢ National Cybersecurity R&D Consortium (Phase 1)

The guidelines of the above grants states that â??no new hires shall be allowed within 6 months before the original project end dateâ??. Our past experience with some projects under other NRF-funded agencies was that replacement hires would be allowed. Below are two examples for illustration - 
â?¢ Example A, Allowable:
(1) there are 2 RF headcounts approved;
(2) there had been 2 RFs hired at one point during the project (before the last 6 months of the project); and
(3) during last 6 months of the project, a new RF is needed to replace one of the previous 2 RFs.
â?¢ Example B, Not allowable:
(1) there are 2 RF headcounts approved; 
(2) there had only been 1 RF hired since the start of the project (before the last 6 months of the project); and
(3) during last 6 months of the project, a new RF is hired for the second position.

Therefore, may we seek NCRâ??s kind advice if this arrangement applies to the listed NCR grants?
