 foreign (non-Singaporean/PR) applicant is hired to fill a Research Fellow position (or any other position which requires a PhD).
â?¢ Nonetheless, PIs should make â??reasonable effortsâ?? to hire Singaporeans/PRs to fill these positions where possible.

In that case, when PIs would like to transfer existing foreigner RFs to the NCR projects, are they still required to put up a brand new job posting BEFORE hiring these foreign candidate(s)?
o These foreigner RFs are already working in Singapore, on other projects (funded by other sources, which may or may not be from NRF).
o The main concern is that such manpower (RFs) with very specific skills and niche expertise are highly sought after, and hence a long transfer process could cause the PIs to lose the critical manpower needed to execute the NCR projects. 

We hope that NRF would be able to shed some light on the definition of â??reasonable effortsâ?? for such scenarios, where the PIs are trying their best to recruit the most suitable research expertise for their NCR projects, by drawing on their existing networks of skilled researchers in this growing field.
