205,"Requests for variations to the awarded grant. Virement between Votes. 21. Grantor delegates the approval authority for the virement of funds between votes to the Host Institution, subject to a cumulative amount not exceeding 10% of the original total project direct cost value. For virements cumulatively above 10%, the approval authority remains with the Grantor. 22. Any virement into the EOM and Research Scholarship votes would require Grantor’s approval, even if the cumulative amount is below 10% of the original total project direct cost value. 23. Inter-institutional virements, where applicable, require the Grantor’s approval and acknowledgement from the director of research (or equivalent) for all Institutions involved. 24. Virement of funds into the Overseas Travel vote is not allowed. Overspending will not be reimbursed. 25. Variation from Research Scholarship vote to other budget category is not allowed, regardless of variation amount.","With regards to the NRF project, Lighting for Facade Applications using Waveguide and Edge Lighting (NRF2015-IIP002-001), we are currently in the midst of seeking for approval from NRF for the request to vire SGD80,000 from the equipment vote to manpower vote.
 
